criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Males or females between 35 and 80 years of age.

          2. Subjects with primary or recurrent symptomatic intracranial arteriosclerosis (stroke
             or transient ischemic attack within 21 days before enrollment, with at least one
             antithrombotic drug and/or vascular risk factors controlled);

          3. Confirmed by DSA: a major intracranial artery (including anterior and posterior
             circulation) stenosis between 70% and 99%, (measured by WASID method), and
             corresponding to clinical symptoms; lesion length≤10mm, diameter≥1.5mm, and the distal
             blood vessel is normal. (For the curvature and angle of the lesion, the investigator
             decides whether it is included in the study according to the actual situation of the
             Subject);

          4. Any of the following methods confirmed that the Subject had insufficient perfusion of
             the area of the lesion in the area of imaging confirmed within 2 weeks before
             surgery:①CTP results showed that cerebral blood flow decreased by more than 30%
             compared with contralateral perfusion of injured lesions;②According to the American
             Society of Interventional and Therapeutic Neuroradiology/Society of Interventional
             Radiology (ASITN/SIR) collateral circulation scoring system, the DSA score is less
             than 3;

          5. Those who voluntarily participate in the study and sign informed consent form.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Those who have surgery within 30 days or plan to perform major surgery within 90 days
             (surgery grade 3 and above);

          2. Those who received thrombolytic therapy within 24 hours before enrollment;

          3. Those with increased neurological symptoms within 24 hours before enrollment;

          4. Subjects of acute ischemic stroke within 3 weeks before enrollment;

          5. In addition to the target vessel and main blood supply artery, there are other
             intracranial artery stenosis more than 70%;

          6. When there is a stenosis in the main blood supply artery of the target vessel, the
             stenosis should be excluded by more than 50%. For example, when the lesion is located
             in the middle cerebral artery, the ipsilateral internal carotid artery stenosis should
             be excluded by >50%; when the lesion is located in the basilar artery, the dominant
             side vertebral artery stenosis >50% should be excluded; non-responsible vascular
             extracranial artery more than 70% should be excluded;

          7. The subjects with tandem lesions;

          8. The mRS baseline score of disabling stroke is more than 3;

          9. Non-atherosclerotic diseases (e.g. arterial dissection, moyamoya disease, vascular
             inflammatory lesions caused by infection, autoimmune diseases, post-irradiation,
             postpartum status; developmental or genetic abnormalities such as fibromuscular
             dysplasia, sickle cell anemia, suspected vasospasm);

         10. The target vessel is severely calcified and closely related to stenosis;

         11. It is suspected that the ischemic event is due to embolism or arterial embolism from
             the extracranial segment (including ipsilateral chest or neck vascular occlusive
             disease) or potential cardiogenic embolism (e.g. atrial fibrillation, mitral stenosis,
             patent foramen ovale, left ventricular thrombus, myocardial infarction within 6 weeks,
             etc.); there are intracranial tumors, aneurysms or intracranial arteriovenous
             malformations;

         12. Those who are allergic to heparin, aspirin, clopidogrel, contrast agents, anesthetics,
             and balloon components;

         13. Hemoglobin is lower than 100g/L, platelet count is less than 100×109/L, international
             normalized ratio (INR) is more than 1.5 (irreversible), coagulation disorders or
             uncorrectable bleeding factors;

         14. Severe liver and kidney dysfunction, ALT is more than 3 times normal value upper limit
             or AST is more than 3 times normal value upper limit, serum creatinine increased more
             than 2 times normal value upper limit;

         15. Pregnant and lactating women;

         16. The survival expectation is less than 1 year;

         17. Those who are unable to complete follow-up because of mental illness, cognitive or
             emotional disorders;

         18. All subjects who are participating in other drug/medical device clinical trials and
             have not completed the programme requirements;

         19. Previous intracranial hemorrhage, including parenchymal hemorrhage, subarachnoid
             hemorrhage, epidural hemorrhage, etc.;

         20. An angioplasty procedure (including balloon dilatation, stenting, or endarterectomy)
             in a previous target vessel or its primary blood supply artery, or a planned stenting
             procedure;

         21. Those who cannot receive dual antiplatelet therapy because of other dieases;

         22. Vascular tortousity cannot stabilize the establishment of vascular access;

         23. Subjects with renal artery, radial artery, and cardiac coronary artery requiring
             concurrent intervention;

         24. Subjects who, in the opinion of the investigators, should not participate in the
             study.
